  "prompt": "Has anyone survived a plane crash?",
  "response": "Yes, many people have survived plane crashes. Aviation is one of the safest modes of transportation, and while accidents are rare, they do occasionally occur. Survival rates in such incidents can vary widely depending on numerous factors, including the nature of the crash, the type of aircraft, weather conditions, and the effectiveness of emergency responses. Here are some notable examples and general information about plane crash survivability:\n\n### **Notable Survivors**\n\n1. **Vesna Vulovi\u0107 (1972)**\n   - **Incident:** JAT Flight 367 exploded over Czechoslovakia due to a bomb.\n   - **Survival Details:** Vesna Vulovi\u0107, a flight attendant, was the sole survivor of the crash. She was trapped by a food cart in the fuselage and miraculously survived a fall from an estimated height of 10,160 meters (33,330 feet), holding the record for surviving the highest fall without a parachute.\n\n2. **Juliane Koepcke (1971)**\n   - **Incident:** LANSA Flight 508 was struck by lightning and disintegrated over the Peruvian rainforest.\n   - **Survival Details:** At 17 years old, Juliane survived the fall from the aircraft and trekked through the jungle for 11 days before being rescued, despite injuries to her back and legs.\n\n3. **Chesley Sullenberger and US Airways Flight 1549 (2009)**\n   - **Incident:** Shortly after takeoff from LaGuardia Airport in New York, both engines failed due to a bird strike.\n   - **Survival Details:** Pilot Chesley \"Sully\" Sullenberger successfully executed an emergency",
